metadata.name: Take Wing #72
metadata.description:
‚ÄúTake Wing‚Äù is a generative art collection depicting the hope, optimism, and thrilling excitement of a person taking off, gaining traction, and soaring to new heights and off into the great unknown.  

The algorithm behind the piece stems from an attempt to go back to art fundamentals and codify composition rules and painterly techniques into a generative form - taking into account focal points, contrast, eye movement, and color theory while still giving the algorithm freedom to explore random color palettes, random flow field movement, random brush strokes, and many other degrees of freedom.

The collection is made in pure code with p5.js and a few GLSL fragment shaders.

The piece has been created to be exhibited at "In Touch" with VerticalCryptoArt in Berlin in September 2022, curated by Anika Meier.

------------------------------------------------

To get a (somewhat) high-resolution output, open the live view of your token, and then edit the URL adding &h=5400 at the end of it.  5400 is the tallest you can go, but you can also put a smaller number if you desire.  Be aware that this will only work on a machine with a very beefy GPU, and even then may take a bit, so please be patient!

metadata.name: The Spectrum Of Nature #198
metadata.description:
*\_../*`¬¨-‚Äô\/*`¬¨‚Äô‚Äô¬¨`*\/‚Äô-¬¨`*\.._/*

Nature, nature, evolving might‚Ä¶ Silent inventor, always right.
Where is the edge of nature and where do we begin?  
What is of nature and what is of man? 
Isn't everything made by nature's hands?

To know more about the concept and technicalities of this piece, see the fxtext article ‚ÄúThe spectrum of nature - a short making of‚Äù. Link at the bottom. If you‚Äôd rather just ignore my personal meaning, feel free to skip the article. 

\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\*\

Basic info:
The piece comes in possible portrait or landscape versions. Both have a relative size of 1 by 1.5. So the initial render will be 1000px wide and 1500px high for portrait. And 1500x1000 for landscape. With the ability to scale this up (see below).

The piece uses WebGL, so will perform much better with a graphics card. A faster computer will obviously be better, though I've done my very best to make it fast and efficient for any old laptop. My hope is that you will find the render process quick and enjoyable for the amount of detail that‚Äôs present. 

../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\../‚Äô`*‚Äô`\..

Controls:
Press the [s] key to save the initial render. You will need to wait a few seconds after all the elements have stopped loading. A box will pop up in the top left saying ‚Äúdone‚Äù for 4 seconds when it‚Äôs ready. For the [s] key to work you may need to open in a new tab. But can right click save otherwise.

Larger sizes:
Press the [2-9] keys to save a resolution of that key size. So [2] saves a 2000x3000 size image, [9] saves a 9000x13500 size image etc. Unless you are making some very large prints you probably won‚Äôt need more than 4k (even 2-3k is big). Though the option is there. 

There may be slight variations in the textures for the larger renders, this is because the shader code has to redraw the textures at the higher pixel resolution, and getting the textures where they sit is more of an art than a science. All the elements remain exact however. 

/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*/*

Made with javascript and some small extra code:
A palette creator by @nathansonic
Noisejs - github.com/josephg/noisejs - Perlin noise generator
Twgl - github.com/greggman/twgl.js - A small webGL helper.

metadata.name: Slumbers #137
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: 0RAL B1NARY: ‚ÄúBINARY ODE‚Äù #31
metadata.description:
An ‚Äúalgorhythmic‚Äù exploration of the oral/aural tradition in poetry. 

‚ÄúZero is a time of night.
Zero is the color of snow.
Zero is the space between notes.
Zero is the silence between words.
Zero is the pause before breath.
Zero is void in the heart of a crowd.
Zero is not nothing, but it‚Äôs not everything.
One is a time of day.
One is the color of spring grass in sunlight.
One is the warmth at the back of my neck when I turn to find you standing there.
One is the rhythm at the base of my spine.
One is the peace at the core of my being.
One is the sound of your voice in the dark.
And one more thing:
Without one I am nothing‚Ä¶‚Äù
‚ÄìTechnelegy 
 

Fusing AI-powered verse, spoken word, original music and visuals all in generative composition, this playful ode to our universal language is inspired by Stiles‚Äô binary-based art and Stern‚Äôs performative poetics. The experiment centers on a transhuman poem by Stiles‚Äô AI alter ego, Technelegy, voiced as zeroes and ones, layered with human- and machine-generated sound ‚Äì evoking ancient data transmissions in the oral tradition as well as the immersive potential of multisensorial, multimedia, metaversal language and literature. Brought into existence via the blockchain, it is a new form of ‚Äútoken word poetry.‚Äù


As with the duo‚Äôs other poetry ‚Äúunreadings,‚Äù all minters will receive an airdropped broadside of the full poem after all editions are collected. A 1/1 media-rich version of the entire poem will also be made available. 
 
Poetic traits:
- 321 editions performed by the algorithm, out of billions of possible combinations
- Each unique piece contains between 3 and 6 (out of 60) lines of generative text from a poem by Technelegy ‚Äì a custom text generator fine-tuned on Stiles‚Äô writing and research material, seeded with prompts from Stiles‚Äô and Stern‚Äôs work ‚Äì translated into binary and performed by Stiles
- 24 possible binary backbeats performed by Stern in his ‚ÄúNathaniel Fun Time‚Äù (NFT) stylings, and generatively re-mixed
- 98 possible intros
- 15 musical stems composed by Kris Bones, generating millions of possible mixes
- Thousands of possible ending combinations 
- 5 fonts, layered in billions of potential ways, including Stern and Stiles‚Äô custom AI font, NNFT (Neural Network Font Type), developed for their ongoing collaboration, ‚ÄúMother Computer‚Äù
- 13 color palettes based on Stern and Stiles‚Äô respective artworka
- Very rare attributes including music-less performance, poem-less music, repeated ‚ÄúB1nary 0de‚Äù (title only)

Click to start and stop or replay. Although the first play through will be the same every time, starting and stopping may create minor variations in your mix (though not any of the core attributes).

0RAL B1NARY: ‚ÄúBINARY ODE‚Äù was produced with partial support from Refraction DAO‚Äôs Creative Grants program, and premiered as part of Refraction Festival at Art Basel Miami 2022. 15% of primary sales go to Refraction, and 5% of primary sales will be donated to Black Girls Code.
